# DFIR Platform API URL
# Set this to connect the portfolio to the DFIR-PLATFORM backend
# Example: http://localhost:8000 or https://your-api.example.com
VITE_DFIR_API_URL=

# When VITE_DFIR_API_URL is empty (default), the portfolio runs in offline mode
# with client-side analysis capabilities. Set a value to enable:
# - Real-time threat intelligence feeds
# - RSS feed aggregation (PacketStorm, BleepingComputer, etc.)
# - Advanced IOC enrichment with external APIs
# - Email/domain analysis with live data sources
